&+Y7DOF Powers Information: Solution to &+WMeta

&+CMeta can be split into 3 sections:

1) Collect all 4 vials to become different animals.
2) Get into Castle Chimera.
3) Become human again and kill the Chimera (main part of the quest).

&+CCollecting the vials

Snake   - Dig at meta1
Bird    - In the branches in meta7
Fish    - In the pool in meta8
Beetle  - At meta8, eat fish vial, pick up bird vial, jump, west, west to 
          waterfall, jump twice, beetle vial is in rocks at the top.
          To get it, put the bird one in the rocks, then get the beetle
          one out (put vial in rocks, get vial from rocks does it). Drop
          the beetle one, it'll fall down the waterfall, now get the bird
          one from the rocks and eat it, then type 'fly'. Go back to
	  meta8, eat the fish vial, jump, west, west again and get the
          beetle vial, go back along to where you jumped in and jump out
          again, eat one of the other vials to stop yourself suffocating on
          land as a fish, and that's the 4 vials  gathered.

&+CGetting into Castle Chimera

   At meta1, eat snake vial and go down.  Go to the snake castle and get
the flask from the king.  Go to the waterfall and fill flask.
Take the flask with water in it to snake beggar and give him it.  He
gives you a pebble.  Get bird vial and eat it at snake beggar and tickle
him, he drops a 2nd pebble.  Now attack him and he runs away in terror
dropping the last pebble.  Take blue pebble and bird vial to meta7, eat
the bird vial, pick up the pebble and fly into the tree. Drop the pebble,
then fly again, get the branch, fly, down, drop branch, light branch with
flame. The flame is created when you drop the pebble, which  shatters
creating the flame. The branch petrifies, now take it to meta14, put the
branch in the mechanism and pull the branch, drawbridge lowers, hey presto,
access to the castle. You can also use the branch as it is, without turning
it to stone first, but it will break after lowering and raising the
drawbridge once.

&+CBecoming Human

In order to become human, you need 5 ingredients to mix in the cauldron.

 1) An alkaline solution.
 2) A golden snake scale.
 3) Some dung.
 4) A silver feather.
 5) A diamond.

There's a book in the zone that explains them all, and why you use them if
you're interested in actually understanding it.

&+CAlkaline Solution

   There is some limestone in an altar in the fish kingdom. If you just
get it from the altar, it will dissolve in the water, so you need to get
the chest from the shelves in the shop in the fish kingdom. It's closed
and watertight, so if you open it, the air will escape. 'turn chest' to
turn it upside down, and open it, the air will stay in.

Go to the altar and get limestone from altar, you put it in the chest
automatically.  Leave the fish kingdom, get the bottle from the shelves
in the storeroom near castle chimera and fill bottle at meta2, meta5 or
meta8 (rooms along by the river) and add the limestone (or the other way
around). It turns into an alkaline solution which you can put in the
cauldron.

&+CGolden Scale

   Get the green pebble from the snake beggar, eat the beetle vial and
smell the pebble, it'll tell you that it smells of tree sap. Become a bird
and in meta7, type 'hit tree' while holding the snake vial, you'll be
arrested and taken into the bird jail. Become a snake in the jail cell,
and wait for the birds to come to put you on trial, when they find a snake
in the cell they flee in terror, leaving you to leave the cell, go down
the tree and take the sap you created when you hit the tree.

   Put sap on pebble, then go back down to the snake kingdom, to meta48
and put pebble in hole. Go to the snake king and get the golden scale as
a reward.

&+CDung

   Dung is in the beetle section of the zone. As a beetle, go up from the
chamber of worship, north into the farmyard, become a snake, go into the
barn, get the dung, go back to where you came up as a beetle, become a
beetle again, go down with the dung, the beetle king will give you a piece
of ancient dung as a reward.

&+CSilver Feather

   Bird in bird shop wants a warm garment, so become a snake and bite
Cottontail, then become a bird and 'skin cottontail'. Take the skin to the
bird shopkeeper and he gives you an orb as thanks. Take the orb to the
bird judge and he'll arrest the shopkeeper who is in fact a thief and
stole the orb, the judge gives you the silver feather as thanks.

   Now take the red pebble from the beggar, and drop it in the same place
you dropped the blue one, up the tree. A red flame is created below. Put
it in the perspex bottle and take it to the cauldron, empty it and light
the kindling with the flame.

&+CDiamond

   The Fish king tells you he'll reward you if you destroy the beaver's
dam which is trapping families away from their homes. To do this you need
to build a bomb. The bomb is made of gunpowder, a vine for a fuse and the
trusty perspex bottle.  

   Gunpowder is in a gun in the farmhouse, near where you got the dung
from. To get it you need to be a bird and 'empty gun'. Put the gunpowder
in the bottle, then get the vine from inside the vines at meta6 as a bird
and put it in the bottle too. Now get the chest you used earlier, light
the bomb with the red flame, put it in the chest, close the chest, leg
it to meta8, become a fish, pick up the chest again (you drop it when
you change form) and go to the dam, drop the chest and swim away as fast
as you can. When the bomb blows up, go to the fish king and he'll give
you the diamond. 

Now take all your ingredients, put them in the cauldron and eat the
resulting liquid, you're human again.

If you eat the liquid at meta70, you get given a staff by a fairy. If you 
don't, you have to go there as a human to get the staff. Go kill Chimera,
if you have the staff his health is lowered and is fairly easy to kill.
Without staff, can't be killed without armour, and you can't take any
into the zone with you.

Having killed Chimera, return to meta70 to be transported out of the
zone and recieve the werewolf spell.

